# Fluff Date: 2026-02-26 19:50:04
<overview>
<p>The Stefan Amaris-class battleship was the Rim Worlds Republic's crowning naval achievement and the only battleship ever produced by a Periphery nation. Directed into existence by President Stefan Amaris himself, the class represented centuries of frustrated ambition finally realized -- the Rim Worlds had been among the first Periphery states to develop capital warships, but the Reunification War had stripped that capability away. While the Republic's shipyards could not match the sheer mass of the Hegemony's McKenna, they produced what became the longest warship ever constructed. The class bore its creator's name without controversy, seen as a symbol of national pride rather than vanity. That perception changed dramatically after the Amaris Coup, when the battleships served as instruments of the Usurper's treachery and earned an enduring stigma that followed the class to its complete extinction.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>Displacing 1,040,000 tons across 1,605 meters of hull, the Stefan Amaris holds the distinction of being the longest warship ever built, though at roughly half the mass of a McKenna it carries correspondingly less firepower. The class compensates with superior armor protection: nearly 1,900 tons of ferro-carbide plating provide better coverage than even the Hegemony's flagship class. Nine Heavy Naval PPCs form the primary capital battery, with three mounted in the nose and three on each broadside. Eight NAC/30 and eight NAC/25 naval autocannons provide devastating broadside fire across the forward, broadside, and aft quarter arcs, while eight Killer Whale capital missile launchers in the forward and aft quarters deliver long-range striking power. A single NAC/40 and two NL45 naval lasers defend the aft arc. Every arc carries identical conventional batteries of three Gauss rifles, four LRM-20 racks, four medium lasers, and four small pulse lasers for anti-fighter defense. Lithium-fusion batteries -- secretly purchased from the Hegemony through Stefan Amaris's manipulation of First Lord Richard Cameron -- allow rapid successive jumps. Four docking collars, thirty-six fighters in two bays, and over 111,000 tons of cargo capacity provide substantial operational flexibility.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>Only five Stefan Amaris-class battleships were ever built, and all five were destroyed within thirteen years of the class entering service. The first three completed hulls received their lithium-fusion battery upgrades at Hegemony shipyards and were on shakedown cruises when the Usurper murdered First Lord Richard Cameron on 27 December 2766. All three immediately played major roles in securing the Hegemony and eliminating SLDF naval forces. The RWS Stefan Amaris herself, the class flagship, was destroyed that same day over the Pacific Ocean by the SLS Enterprise, a McKenna-class battleship, during the fierce eighteen-hour orbital battle above Terra. The fourth and fifth hulls -- RWRS Gregory Amaris and RWRS Terens Amaris -- were still under construction when the SLDF conquered the Rim Worlds Republic. General Kerensky ordered both vessels completed and renamed: the SLS Vengeance and SLS Chieftain. The Vengeance served with Admiral Akkayev-Cameron's Fourth Fleet and was destroyed during the assault on New Home in early 2775. The Chieftain met a more celebrated end, leading Task Force Leonidas during Operation LIBERATION in January 2777 -- a forty-ship suicide mission that destroyed 106 Caspar drone warships over forty-two hours of continuous combat before every vessel in the task force was annihilated.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The Stefan Amaris-class battleship emerged from centuries of frustrated Rim Worlds Republic naval ambition. The Republic had been among the first Periphery nations to develop true capital warships, but the devastating Reunification War forced them to abandon those efforts. When Stefan Amaris ascended to the presidency, he brought renewed focus to his admirals' long-standing desire for a modern warship fleet. While the Republic initially contented itself with purchasing mothballed Star League designs and producing copies of existing vessels -- most of which proved less efficient and more problematic than their originals -- Amaris demanded something grander: the Human Sphere's premier battleship.</p><p>Rockwell-Vasquez Starcraft at Zertarum could not deliver the most massive warship ever built as Amaris had hoped, but they designed an effective battlewagon that claimed the record for the longest at 1,605 meters. Massing just over half of the Hegemony's McKenna, the Stefan Amaris was better armored but otherwise paled in comparison to that king of all warships. Amaris achieved his greatest coup prior to the assassination of Richard Cameron by manipulating the young First Lord into selling lithium-fusion battery systems for the new battleships -- a technology that dramatically enhanced their strategic mobility.</p><p>The first three hulls were completed and upgraded with LF batteries at Hegemony shipyards, ostensibly on shakedown cruises when Amaris launched his coup on 27 December 2766. All three immediately participated in securing the Terran Hegemony and destroying SLDF naval forces. The RWS Stefan Amaris was destroyed that same day above Terra by the SLS Enterprise and her escorts during the savage eighteen-hour orbital battle. Two more hulls remained under construction in the Rim Worlds; after the SLDF conquered the Republic, Kerensky ordered both completed and renamed the SLS Vengeance and SLS Chieftain. The Vengeance served with the Fourth Fleet and was destroyed at New Home in early 2775 during Operation CHIEFTAIN. The Chieftain earned a heroic legacy by leading Task Force Leonidas in January 2777 -- a forty-ship formation on a deliberate suicide mission to clear Caspar drone warships from the Sol system ahead of Operation LIBERATION. Over forty-two brutal hours, the task force destroyed 106 drones, roughly forty percent of those in the system, before every ship was annihilated. None of the five Stefan Amaris-class battleships survived the liberation of the Terran Hegemony, and the class passed into history bearing both the Usurper's stigma and the heroism of the crews who turned his weapons against his legacy.</p>
</history>

